children.text: The hebel in this area has a penetration through the panel that has not been sealed, which will possibly allow water and pest ingress, and will also reduce the thermal and acoustic performance of the Hebel panel system.
The Hebel Power Panel external wall design and installation instructions state in section 3.3 Installation of Services, that
'Penetrations through the PowerPanelXL panel for services should be neatly filled and the joint sealed with an external grade acoustic and/or fire rated paintable sealant' .
This must be properly rectified to prevent failure of the Hebel system, prior to works in this area proceeding any further.
